HEADWORD: Ocypodian
<hw>O`cy*po"di*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>'wky`s</grk> swift
+ <grk>poy`s</grk>, <grk>podo`s</grk>, foot.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of a tribe of crabs which live in holes in the sand along the
seashore, and run very rapidly, -- whence the name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

